The paper discusses a neuromorphic computational framework for embedded learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning algorithms, including deep learning, which are commonly associated with the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the framework in mobile systems, wearable devices, and robots, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-categories.
